The paper deals with network coding, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It specifically focuses on directed acyclic networks, which are commonly studied in network information theory (cs.NI). The paper also discusses linear network coding, which is a technique used in network information theory and communication complexity (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper touches on the insufficiency of linear network coding and unachievability of network coding capacity, which are topics in distributed systems (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC), respectively.
